briefdescription.para: Function for calculating the partial of the acceleration w.r.t. the position of body undergoing acceleration..

detaileddescription.para:
Function for calculating the partial of the acceleration w.r.t. the position of body undergoing acceleration and adding it to the existing partial block Update( ) function must have been called during current time step before calling this function.
partialMatrix
Block of partial derivatives of acceleration w.r.t. Cartesian position of body undergoing acceleration where current partial is to be added.
addContribution
Variable denoting whether to return the partial itself (true) or the negative partial (false).
startRow
First row in partialMatrix block where the computed partial is to be added.
startColumn
First column in partialMatrix block where the computed partial is to be added.

briefdescription.para: Function to compute the partial w.r.t. time-independent empirical acceleration components.

detaileddescription.para:
Function to compute the partial w.r.t. time-independent empirical acceleration components from list of components and functional shapes.
numberOfAccelerationComponents
Total number of empirical acceleration components w.r.t. which partials are to be computed.
accelerationIndices
Map denoting list of components of accelerations that are to be computed. Key: functional shape of empirical accelerations. Value: list of acceleration vaector entries that are to be used (0: radial (R), 1: along-track (S), 2: cross-track (W)).
partialDerivativeMatrix
Matrix of partial derivatives of accelerations w.r.t. empirical accelerations (returned by reference)
